                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6542.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                            Juarez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juárez</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All attempts to hold a peace conference on American soil having failed, a special
                    train carrying a number of self-appointed peace commissioners departed for
                    Mexico City to-day. None of the active late insurrectos were in the party.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
